# Consensus Engine: Requirements & Dependencies

This document provides a clean, consolidated list of the primary dependencies required to run the Consensus Engine project. 

## 1. Backend API (Python 3.10+)
The backend is a fast, asynchronous API built with **FastAPI** and uses **SQLAlchemy** for database ORM.

**Core Framework & Server:**
- `fastapi` & `uvicorn` (Web Framework & ASGI Server)
- `pydantic` & `pydantic-settings` (Data Validation & Config)

**Database & ORM:**
- `sqlalchemy` (ORM)
- `alembic` (Migrations)
- `asyncpg` & `psycopg2-binary` (PostgreSQL Drivers)
- `aiosqlite` (Async SQLite Driver)

**Auth & Security:**
- `python-jose[cryptography]` (JWT Tokens)
- `passlib[bcrypt]` (Password Hashing)

**AI & External Services:**
- `litellm` (LLM Routing/Standardization)
- `firebase-admin` (Firebase Integration)
- `redis` (Caching)
- `boto3` (AWS SDK)

---

## 2. Frontend Web App (Node.js & Next.js)
The frontend is a modern React application built on **Next.js 14**, styled with **Tailwind CSS**, and features heavy 3D visualizations using **Three.js**.

**Core Framework:**
- `next` (v14.0.1)
- `react` & `react-dom` (v18)

**UI & Styling:**
- `tailwindcss` (v3.3.5)
- `lucide-react` (Icons)
- `framer-motion` (Fluid Animations)
- `clsx` & `tailwind-merge` (Class Management)

**3D Rendering (WebGL):**
- `three`
- `@react-three/fiber`
- `@react-three/drei`

**Editor & Services:**
- `@monaco-editor/react` (Code Editor)
- `firebase` (Client SDK)

---

## Running the Application
**Backend:**
\`\`\`bash
cd apps/api
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
\`\`\`

**Frontend:**
\`\`\`bash
cd apps/web
npm install
npm run dev
\`\`\`
